parameters: Turns out this isn't a shelf. It's a painting of a shelf.
It feels like it's nailed to the shelves.
It's an old tiki bar that was converted into a booth for the summer reading program.
There's a roll of cheap paper tickets on the table.
When I was a kid they gave you a ticket for every number of pages you read during the summer.
After that you could trade them in for prizes.
It's not summer, but I don't think it'll hurt to take a prize ticket.
